Title: Great product...
Review:
Pros:

I've used M20x, M30x but M50x is more comfortable.

Cusion is much softer than others.

Sounds rich, we can hear each & every sound with great detail.

Lows feels very nice and neutral or without any enhancement.

Panning is in detail.

3 cables included, which is really good for use in different conditions. Unlike other studio monitors, we can use the short cable with phone.

Connection of cable with headphones is great, twist to fit type, so the cable can't accidentally come out.

Good quality leather pouch is provided.

Cons:

After every use you have to remove the cable, so that it could fit in the pouch.

It feels like the sound is not neutral especially highs feel enhanced in certain types of music or songs.

Overall, If you are a professional, go for it, if you are amateur, lower versions will do the job.

Title: Such a magical book that's why strongly recommend to every classic lover (reader) !!
Review:
" Reading the Alchemist was like getting up at dawn and seeing the sun rise while the rest of the world still slept." I've read all type of books but 'The Alchemist' is so different in every aspects.
üîñ
*Book Review*
~
The Alchemist- By Paulo Coelho.
üîñ
The cover of the book is simple,decent and focusing at the main plot of the story. The book is a light read of approx 160 pages where the author impeccably written the story with very impressive narration, plot and characters. This great book have changed my way of thinking about goals and destiny, completely.
üîñ
"Every man kills the thing he loves."
~
The story revolves around a young boy, a shepherd who wants to fulfill his dream to see the great pyramids and find the treasure, that he had seen in his dream. So he went to reach his destiny and in doing so, he met different new souls who helped him to complete his journey to see the pyramids and the treasure.
üîñ
"Your eyes show the strength of your soul."
~
He met with a desert girl, Fatima and both fell in love with each other. Later he met with main character of the story, an Alchemist who educated him about the alchemy and helped to achieve his dream. During the journey, the boy learnt many lessons of the desert.
üîñ
The author have so brilliantly written this book with an amazing plots and lessons that i have finished it in less than a day. I strongly recommend this magical piece to every reader who wants to pick their next read (classic).
I'm sure after reading this book you will come to know that "There is only one thing that makes a dream impossible to achieve: the fear of failure."
üîñ
My ratings- 5/5 ‚≠ê

Title: The Alchemist focuses on "dreams are made to be followed".
Review:
Reading ‚ÄúThe Alchemist‚Äù feels less like reading a book and more like sitting around a fire in the desert listening to an ancient story being passed down through oral tradition. Despite its meaningful content, ‚ÄúThe Alchemist‚Äù is a very quick and easy read.

Through Santiago‚Äôs journey to treasure and love and travel, Coelho encourages readers to not only discover their own dreams for their lives, but also to never give up pursuing them.

It also offers a simple message to readers that is also one of the most profound considerations of life which is our purpose in this world.

Title: Good replacement for J series in this price tag
Review:
Fair review after one week of usage:
Pros: 1. The display quality and size is quite very nice. The cover i would suggest is Spigen Hybrid case for a complete protection.
2. The fingerprint sensor is fast.
3. The latest android 10 provides it with vast features.
4. The trending USB Type C port is latest compared to other lower range samsung phones.
5. The ocean blue colour makes a premium feel in hand.
6. Battery life is quite very good.
7. The expandable storage through micro sd is quite appreciable.
8. The processor is fast and good for gaming.
9. It competes with other samsung phones and is a good replacement for J series in terms of features, speed, processor and ram.
Cons: 1. No back cover and earphones are provided by samsung with this phone which isn‚Äôt expected. Though all the lower range phones of other brands have these basic things.
2. The back panel is polymide plastic which could have been a glass one to give it a premium feel like in Redmi note 8 Pro which too has almost the same price tag.
3. The face unlock does not always recognise the face and have to work with fingerprint or other methods of unlock.
4. The display seems to be fragile and prone to scratches and cracks if hybrid case and tampered is not used.
5. The charging is a bit slow.
6. The phone lags sometimes while unlocking through lock screen which isn‚Äôt expected with this processor and android version.
7. The sound output could have been more.
8. The fingerprint sensor is located too above on the back panel.
9. The camera quality is average and could have been much better as compared to other brands with this price.
The phone could have been a beast if these features were improved by samsung. I will conclude by saying, Its a very good phone in this price tag if these cons does not matter your day to day usage. Though its the best phone in all the lower range series of samsung.

Title: Pretty decent cans for a right price!
Review:
Well i am going to breakdown my review into few parts :-

1} COMFORT
I bought these in month of Jan (2020). It was cold during that time so these provided a good snugly warm feel but soon i noticed that as time passed temp started to rise resulting in sweat during summertime. I have to take them off after 1 hr of usage and wipe sweat which is pretty inconvenient. I would also like to add the fact that my ears are big and due to that i can't wear them for long without having pain. If you have big ears just get extra pair of pads. Also i would like to add that you can not listen comfortablely if you are outside.

2}SOUND QUALITY
The most important part!! If you are upgrading from 4-5 k(INR) range then you will feel considerable upgrade. Sound stange is not big everything feels like its "in your head" . Note that sound separation is good not sound stage. Now lets come to detail retrieval, highs are boosted which make them strike a bit hard in some tracks like edm which is boosted already for "majority" but if you listen to guitar acoustic tracks you are gonna love it. Mids are recessed and not warm in short mids lack energy. While sub bass is adequately "boomy". Bass near low mid region is tight and edm tracks sound great in that region. Using eq is highly recommended if you listen to variety of genres.

3} PRICING
I got mine for 8 k (INR) which was a steal if you are getting around that price go for them. They provide a good value for that price.

4} EASE OF TRAVEL
This is the part where M-50x's shine real well. There foldable design provide great use during traveling. Moreover they are just 38 ohm so they can be powered using smartphone or laptop whithout need of buying portable amp. Also there are 3 cables provided which come hande time to time.
If you've made this far,
Thank You for reading

Title: Here, we are reading our history.
Review:
This is about homo sapiens. The only living human tribe. This is about Us.

It is always interesting to learn our history. How we got transformed from ancient foragers to present day humans. Obviously that transformation was not smooth, may be not intentional as well. It was a continuous process, evolution. We can say, it is still happening. Who knows, what will be the changes happening to human race after 1000 or 5000 years.

Sapiens is all about the evolution process of species homo sapiens. Role of cognitive, agricultural, industrial and scientific revolutions on it. Major achievements and pitfalls of those processes. The interesting part is that author got connected the points in our history using his perspectives. Readers have complete freedom for accepting or not. But it is worth reading.

Title: 4.5 stars for the TV, 5 Stars for the delivery
Review:
I am a loyal prime user of Amazon and shop frequently. Never have been disspointed with the delivery and if at all I was not happy with the product, support team of amazon would always help me out.
So this time too the delivery was smooth and on schedule.
The Sony service center team did call us but I had already installed the TV by myself as it was pretty simple. Service center team came to our house and delivered the wall mount panel and also they informed that they will do free mounting . I didn't require the mounting at that time.

Finally about the product.

Display, viewing angles and Sound quality is good. But would suggest people to get a good soundbar for good cinematic experience. (always recommended for any TV).
The TV comes with smart features. It has dedicated YouTube and Netflix button on the remote. It has apps like prime, zee, yupp, Eros now, etc. I want to install Hotstar app but not sure if it is possible.
The only issue is the smart tv interface is too laggy. I guess the RAM is not sufficient enough. Other than that playback happens super smooth which depends on a good wifi connection.

So for a 43" TV 38k is a bit high considering Chinese competitors like one plus giving at a much cheaper cost. But I paid a premium for a non Chinese company, Sony, which is also a made in India product and I have not qualms about it.

Update: one cannot install additional apps on any "Smart TV". It has to be an "Android TV" for any new application installation

Title: Nothing beats this!!
Review:
Being a musician I was in two minds over whether I should go for this or other similar products from Sennheiser and the likes.
You'll come across many reviews that deem this wonder of a headphone a waste, not upto the mark, not bass heavy, dirt cheap in ears being better sounding an all.
People who dish out such verdicts are doing a great deal of disservice to the audiophile community simply because they are being stupid, ignorant and biased.

Coming to the technical aspects now there's not much that hasn't already been mentioned in other reviews.

If you want clarity and have the minimum requisite common sense and knowledge of tweaking an equaliser then this is by far and large the best headphone you can ever have in a sub 10k range.

Please understand that a song's characteristics make it bass heavy or crisp in its mids or shrill in its highs. What you hear is almost a filter (the processing circuitry of a headphone) applied to the output (the audio signal from your device) when you listen to a song on earphones and headphones. If it's already tweaked to sound bass heavy, there's not much room left for other frequencies to surface.

This headphone almost reproduces the exact signal that it receives. Almost, because truth be told there are other contenders in higher price brackets that perform way better than this.

Go for it if you still want crystal clear clarity and also want headroom for tweak-ability while you're at it.

Title: Don't fall for the hype!
Review:
I have read quite a number of books that ended up disappointing me. Some of those were gifted by well-meaning friends. Some of them were books I bought on an impulse. Then there were books that I had waited years to read only to find them unworthy of all those years of patience. But this book by Yuval Noah Harari tops the list. Just imagine reading a book that all your friends were going gaga about, only to find that there is nothing worthwhile in it and wondering whether you are really a good reader at all, now that you don‚Äôt even like a book that the whole world around you seems to love!

Let‚Äôs clear a few things first, before you think of bashing me up. This is a commendable effort by Mr. Harari to summarize the whole history of mankind and its evolutionary tale. During the initial pages, I too thought that this will be one of the best reads on anthropology. But this book promises a lot only to deceive. We statisticians use the term confirmation bias, which means the tendency to favor and present only those information that are supportive to one‚Äôs beliefs. This book is full of them. Harari had decided to present all that is wicked and weak about Homo Sapiens and he has succeeded to a large extent.

Not that I am complaining. I for one have never held the notion that we humans are special beings sitting atop the food chain, placed there by a favorable god who created us all in his (or, is it a ‚Äòher‚Äô?) own image. I think of us as a different species of apes that managed to evolve a little quicker than our cousins. Despite our use of advanced languages, costly clothes and snazzy gadgets, internally we remain the beasts that roamed the vast forests once. I see nothing special about being human. This book helped cement that belief in my mind by discussing the idiocies and idiosyncrasies of our species as a whole.

But that‚Äôs just about it. This book isn‚Äôt ‚Äòa brief history of humankind‚Äô, but the opinions of Mr. Harari about the various aspects of human evolution. This isn‚Äôt a chronological history in the lines of ‚ÄòWhat on Earth Happened?‚Äô by Christopher Lloyd or ‚ÄòA Short History of Nearly Everything‚Äô by Bill Bryson, both of which I found to be far more informative and interesting than this one. This is both a philosophical take and passing of judgments by Mr. Harari on what he considers to be the vital cogs of human evolution, namely Cognitive Revolution, Agricultural Revolution & Scientific Revolution. There is nothing that you end up learning that you already didn‚Äôt learn, especially in case you had read those two aforementioned books.

Sorry, dear friends. I have read much better books. 2.5 stars!
TitleText: do n't fall for the hype !
ReviewText: \ n i have read quite a number of books that ended up disappointing me . some of those were gifted by well-meaning friends . some of them were books i bought on an impulse . then there were books that i had waited years to read only to find them unworthy of all those years of patience . but this book by yuval noah harari tops the list . just imagine reading a book that all your friends were going gaga about , only to find that there is nothing worthwhile in it and wondering whether you are really a good reader at all , now that you do n't even like a book that the whole world around you seems to love ! \ n \ nlet 's clear a few things first , before you think of bashing me up . this is a commendable effort by mr . harari to summarize the whole history of mankind and its evolutionary tale . during the initial pages , i too thought that this will be one of the best reads on anthropology . but this book promises a lot only to deceive . we statisticians use the term confirmation bias , which means the tendency to favor and present only those information that are supportive to one 's beliefs . this book is full of them . harari had decided to present all that is wicked and weak about homo sapiens and he has succeeded to a large extent . \ n \ nnot that i am complaining . i for one have never held the notion that we humans are special beings sitting atop the food chain , placed there by a favorable god who created us all in his ( or , is it a ‚Äò her ' ? ) own image . i think of us as a different species of apes that managed to evolve a little quicker than our cousins . despite our use of advanced languages , costly clothes and snazzy gadgets , internally we remain the beasts that roamed the vast forests once . i see nothing special about being human . this book helped cement that belief in my mind by discussing the idiocies and idiosyncrasies of our species as a whole . \ n \ nbut that 's just about it . this book is n't ‚Äò a brief history of humankind ' , but the opinions of mr . harari about the various aspects of human evolution . this is n't a chronological history in the lines of ‚Äò what on earth happened ? ' by christopher lloyd or ‚Äò a short history of nearly everything ' by bill bryson , both of which i found to be far more informative and interesting than this one . this is both a philosophical take and passing of judgments by mr . harari on what he considers to be the vital cogs of human evolution , namely cognitive revolution , agricultural revolution & scientific revolution . there is nothing that you end up learning that you already did n't learn , especially in case you had read those two aforementioned books . \ n \ nsorry , dear friends . i have read much better books . 2 . 5 stars ! \ n

Title: Easy to setup, great sound quality, best for beginners.
Review:
First of all to all those thinking that it is a counterfit or a first copy product because you got it with mini USB 5 pin port instead of a big USB type B, let me tell you it is 100% original. USB Type B is an older port and is replaced by mini usb 5 pin B which this mic would now come with. Mine was usb mini as mentioned and I was successfully able to register my product serial number with Logitech (Since Blue company is now acquired by Logitech). Even Blue Sherpa Companion app was able to find my mic with correct serial number. So relax it is original only.
Now for the review part-
1. Amazon packaging was pathetic the box was damaged, they sent me the box in a white amazon polythene instead of packing it inside a cardboard box. Not sure what happened here usually Amazon pack things nicely so I guess it was the seller (Bought it from prime seller). However luckily my mic was not damaged. (Touchwood)
2. Talking about mic itself, it is simply amazing, It captures the lows, the mids and the highs perfectly without any problems.
3. Noise cancellation is okay, not best for sure but very decent, live streaming should not be a problem at all and if you are using it for voice overs you can post process it in either audacity or premier pro to make it sound like a professional studio mic.
4. The wire sent with the mic was black for some reason even though my mic was white but it still looks absolutely stunning sitting on your desk, clubs very well with the setup, definitely an eye catcher.
5. Stand provided with it is sturdy and has nice rubber feet so it will not slip off easily and will hold it‚Äôs position.
 Overall a great mic even in 2020 for beginners and growing youtubers, definitely gives you a professional edge without putting a whole in your pocket. I bought it during covid so costed me around 5k but you should be able to find a good deal on this, though it‚Äôs still worth it at 5k considering the sound it‚Äôs amazing sound quality. Would have given 5 stars but had to cut 1 star for packaging.

If you‚Äôre looking for a condenser mic which is easy to setup and is bang for your buck, look no further and buy this. You will not regret.

Thanks for taking time out to read my review. Stay safe, be healthy and take care.

Title: Best phone in the range,Go for it.
Review:
After uses 15 days. I will give the review of Samsung Galaxy M31 is a brilliant smartphone. It's display is better than any other phone in this range. Cameras are very good. Battery is extreme. Performance is just at par not that good. Software the OneUI 2.0 is very good Android skin. Design wise, it's very well designed and built quality is very good as well. charging. Time approximately 2hr.

So, overall a brilliant smartphone under INR 16.499,
*Ratings are according to price i.e. 10 means best in the range not the overall best*.

Design - 9/10 Good looks, brilliant built quality, very comfortable to hold with slightly curved edges.

Display - 10/10 Brilliant, crisp and very bright display. 6.4 Inch FHD+ sAmoled display with Corning Gorilla Glass 3 protection. The display from different viewing angles is beautiful.

Software - 9/10 OneUI 2.0 based on Android 10. Very good software with very less ads

Hardware/Performance - 8/10 Decent performance. It comes with Samsung's Exynos 9611 chipset. It scores around 191391 on Antutu Benchmark which is just at par score. So, not that good but still decent performance)

Battery - 10/10 (6000 mAh monster battery life with 15 W fast charger which takes around 2 hours to charge the huge battery. While the battery life is very solid, it can easily work for two days.)

Camera - 8.5/10

Rear - 8/10 (64MP main camera with f/1.8 aperture which captures brilliant detailed photos in daylight but struggles a bit in low light conditions. 8MP Ultra Wide-angle camera with f/2.2 aperture captures good photos in daylight but is of no use in the night. 5MP macro lens captures brilliant macros but again not for the night. Lastly a 5MP depth sensor which clicks brilliant portraits in both daylight and low light. Video quality is good and stable at 1080p while it lacks stability at 4K. But overall good camera.
Front - 9/10 32MP camera with f/2.0 aperture. It clicks beautiful selfies in both daylight as well as low light.)
Value For Money - 9/10 (At INR 16499, it offers one of the best display, monster battery life, decent performance and good cameras.

Title: Mind-boggling!!! Awesome!!!
Review:
Well, i usually refrain from writing reviews of books online but this one was so amazing that i think it's worth taking out time to write a review for this. That being said, this book is a complete gem. Not only for the knowledge and deep understanding of the nationalism (of Japan, West & India) that it imparts but also the general statements made by Rabindranath Tagore in his speeches about life, machines, human-machines, problems of human races throughout the world & India in pre & post colonial times and the true and real meaning and need of government in today's era.

NOTE: The book is NOT WRITTEN by Rabindranath Tagore but rather is a compilation of various speeches by him. Nevertheless, his diction is classic.

This was my first reading of Tagore, and this completely justified to me why this legend is a Literature Nobel Laureate.

So once again I formatted my SSD (MBR partition Style) and installed new Windows Using Pen-Drive (Media Creation Tool) , and my issue got resolved, windows got installed in *New SSD within 1 hour* .
Then I deletes my OS and reserved partition from HDD and add-on that space to HDD.

Title: Excellent SSD for Reasonable Price...
Review:
SSD performance is good, all metal body and durable. I installed fresh windows 10 in around 12 minutes, same install process would take around 30 minutes in HDD. Now I'm able to login windows in just under 30 seconds, with my old HDD login would take around 2 to 3 minutes.

Now I can carry my Lenovo yoga laptop without worrying about damaging the HDD.

This SSD made in Malaysia. Not sure about the 5 years warranty hope nothing bad happens.

Professional and heavy users must install the Crucial Stroage Executive software to get more out of this SSD.
